---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Agent Integration">
  <h1>Agent integration</h1>
  <p class="muted">Use the MCP server when an agent needs snapshots and actions through one protocol.</p>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>MCP setup</h2>
    <pre>brna mcp --metro http://localhost:8081</pre>
    <p>The server exposes the current snapshot as <code>brna://current/snapshot</code> and action tools for <code>tap</code>, <code>type</code>, <code>scroll</code>, <code>swipe</code>, <code>long_press</code>, and <code>key</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Selector flow</h2>
    <p>Read the snapshot, choose a selector such as <code>#save</code> or <code>button:Submit</code>, then call the matching action tool. The MCP server resolves selectors with the same engine as the CLI before posting to Metro.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Suggested selectors</h2>
    <p>
      Each node in the snapshot carries a canonical <code>selector</code> and
      an ordered list of <code>suggested_selectors</code>. The first entry of
      <code>suggested_selectors</code> always equals <code>selector</code>;
      every entry in the list resolves uniquely to that node, so an agent can
      copy any of them verbatim into a <code>brna act</code> call.
    </p>
    <p>Suggestions are emitted in priority order:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><code>#&lt;id&gt;</code> when the node has a stable id (testID or accessibilityIdentifier).</li>
      <li><code>@&lt;testID&gt;</code> as a syntactic alternate for stable-id nodes.</li>
      <li><code>&lt;role&gt;:&lt;name&gt;</code> when role and name resolve uniquely.</li>
      <li><code>&lt;role&gt;:__&lt;name&gt;__</code> when an inferred icon/group label is also available in its raw exact form.</li>
      <li><code>&lt;role&gt;:&lt;name&gt; in #&lt;ancestor&gt;</code> when role/name needs scoping.</li>
      <li><code>&lt;text&gt;...&lt;text&gt;</code> as a readable text-fragment fallback.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>The list is capped at four entries per node. Agents should prefer the
       first entry (<code>selector</code>) and fall back to alternates only when
       they need a more readable form.</p>
  </section>
</Base>
